cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for semantic segmentation of 3D medical images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach for efficient processing of 3D data, which involves down-shuffling and convolution operations. This could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
